article.headline: Colorado St. 93, Chadron State 50
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. -- Colton Iverson led five double-figure scorers with 18 points on Thursday night and Colorado State rolled to a 93-50 victory over Chadron State. Iverson also had nine rebounds for Colorado State (2-0). Pierce Hornung scored 11 points with nine rebounds and six steals. Greg Smith scored 14 points for the Rams, with Jon Octeus scoring 13 and Gerson Santo 12. The Rams scored 21 points off of turnovers. Chadron State (0-2) scored just 13 points in the first half. David Downey led Chadron State with 15 points, including 4-of-6 shooting from 3-point range. Colorado State also had a 48-26 scoring advantage off the bench.
